<span id="freeTextContainer7274570178805824932">One of the most beautiful books I have ever read and re-read a thousand times. For a long time, Totto-Chan defined the ideal childhood for me. It&apos;s been almost 15 years since I last read it but I still remember Takahashi, Osaka, Master Kobayashi and many more. <br/><br/>Totto-Chan was one of my most intimate (albeit imaginary)childhood friends. Read this book to go back to the halcyon, carefree, sun-lit days of those innocent years. </span>
