              <span id="reviewTextContainer3544501846" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8068594805695534428">If you don&apos;t already know, it was bliss to see Totto-chan with her friends having childhood adventures. <i>Bliss</i>.<br/><br/>This is a memoir by Tetsuko Kuroyanagi about her childhood when she was in a quite peculiar school named Tomoe Gakuen and run by Mr. Sosaku Kobayashi.<br/><br/>I have never really known much about the past Japan traditions and cultures apart from some <i>Doraemon</i> or <i>Shin-chan</i> (courtesy to my younger sister).<br/><br/>But this was beautiful. And picturesque. <br/><br/><img src='https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1611842686ra/30772098.gif' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/><blockquote>
<img src='https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1611287163i/30736931._SX540_.jpg' class='gr-hostedUserImg'/><br/><br/>𝕜𝕖𝕪 𝕥𝕙𝕠𝕦𝕘𝕙𝕥𝕤<br/><i>→ innocence<br/>→ love<br/>→ motherhood<br/>→ creativit</i></blockquote></span>
  <span id="freeText8068594805695534428" style="display:none">If you don't already know, it was bliss to see Totto-chan with her friends having childhood adventures. <i>Bliss</i>.<br><br>This is a memoir by Tetsuko Kuroyanagi about her childhood when she was in a quite peculiar school named Tomoe Gakuen and run by Mr. Sosaku Kobayashi.<br><br>I have never really known much about the past Japan traditions and cultures apart from some <i>Doraemon</i> or <i>Shin-chan</i> (courtesy to my younger sister).<br><br>But this was beautiful. And picturesque. <br><br><img src="https://images.gr-assets.com/hostedimages/1611842686ra/30772098.gif" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br><blockquote>
<img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1611287163i/30736931._SX540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>𝕜𝕖𝕪 𝕥𝕙𝕠𝕦𝕘𝕙𝕥𝕤<br><i>→ innocence<br>→ love<br>→ motherhood<br>→ creativity<br>→ school classrooms in railways<br>→ eurythmics</i><br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1611287163i/30736931._SX540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg">
</blockquote><br><br>Totto-chan's school is Tomoe Gakuen, run by Mr. Sosaku Kobayashi who loves children whole-heartedly and always wants to bring out the best in them. The classrooms are train boxes, and at lunch, you're supposed to bring <i>something from the ocean and something from the hills</i>.<br><br><blockquote>
  <i>
    <b>“Down through the ages and in the whole world, Watt and Newton cannot have been the only ones to notice the steam from a boiling kettle or observe an apple fall. Having eyes, but not seeing beauty; having ears, but not hearing music; having minds, but not perceiving truth; having hearts that are never moved and therefore never set on fire. These are the things to fear, said the headmaster.”</b>
  </i>
</blockquote><br><br>Reading about the school through the grown-up but child's eyes made everything amusing and interesting. Moreover, the children are just around 6 or 7-years-old, and just seeing them go through their daily lives makes it even better.<br><br>I love Totto-chan's innocence and seeing her reflect on her younger self is gratifying. And I love the amusing third-person writing (despite this being a memoir) that analyzes the characters.<br><br><blockquote>
  <b>
    <i>“But there’s no doubt that children have an innate sense of humor. No matter how young they are, they always know when something’s really funny.”</i>
  </b>
</blockquote><br><br>It was fast-paced (of course!) and I devoured it in a couple of lucky days. 🤘<br><br><blockquote>
  <img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1611287163i/30736931._SX540_.jpg" class="gr-hostedUserImg">
</blockquote><br><br>I would definitely recommend this, to anyone!<br><br>~Happy Reading!<br><br><a href="https://aarjakochar.carrd.co/" rel="nofollow noopener">
  <img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1611851318i/30773386.png" class="gr-hostedUserImg">
</a></span>
  <a data-text-id="8068594805695534428" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

